  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of essential life-saving Health, Nutrition, WASH and Child Protection interventions to vulnerable girls, boys, women and men affected by drought in the Arid and Semi-Arid Land (ASAL) counties of Kenya</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNICEF is implementing its life-saving activities in the drought-affected Arid and Semi-Arid (ASAL) counties by strategically collaborating with implementing partners, community volunteers, and county governments to provide critical Nutrition, WASH, Health, and Child-protection services. During the 12 months implementation period of this $2.35 million allocation, UNICEF will provide increased access to safe drinking water and improved hygiene services to 200,100 people in the six most-affected counties, among which above 50% are women and girls. Additionally, the project will provide life-saving health interventions to 55,644 newborn children, preventive household care training to 350 community health extension workers and volunteers, therapeutic feeding to 32,899 people (49% girls), and protection support to 13,733 children.</narrative>
  </description>
